ww.cardiffbay.co.uk/index.php/en/wife-on-the-ocean|url-status=dead|archive-date=17 October 2013|title=''Wife on the Ocean Wave''|work=Cardiff Bay|accessdate=17 October 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Cardiff-Bay-World-Harmony-Peace-Statue.jpg|75px]]\n! ''World Harmony Peace Statue''<br>{{small|Statue of [[Sri Chinmoy]]}}\n| Statue\n| Waterfront Park\n| 2012\n| {{sort|Torpy|Kaivalya Torpy}}\n| {{centre|{{--}}}}\n| Unveiled 11 March 2012 to mark the 25th anniversary of the [[Peace Run|World Harmony Run]].\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=World Harmony Peace Statue in Cardiff|url=http://www.srichinmoybio.co.uk/news/peace/world-harmony-peace-statue-in-cardiff/|publisher=Sri Chinmoy Centre|accessdate=30 May 2014|date=13 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanderkrogt.net/statues/object.php?webpage=ST&record=gbwa016|title=World Harmony Peace Statue|work=Statues \u2013 Hither & Thither|first1=Ren\u00e9|last1=van der Krogt|first2=Peter|last2=van der Krogt|accessdate=28 September 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Art and Sole Survivor - geograph.org.uk - 774993.jpg|75px]]\n! ''Yellow Bench''\n| Sculpture\n| Longueil Close\n| 1999\n| {{sort|Rowe|Andrew Rowe}}\n| {{centre|{{--}}}}\n|\n|<ref name=\"CPAR 58\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |title=Cardiff Public Art Register |publisher=Cardiff Council |year=2011 |page=58 |accessdate=25 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205093528/https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |archivedate=5 December 2014 }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Cathays==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Image\n! {{nobreak|Title / individual}} commemorated\n! Type\n! Location\n! Date\n! Sculptor\n! {{nobreak|Architect /}} Designer\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Source\n|-\n|-\n| [[File:Saint Michael triumphant over the Devil.jpg|75px]]\n! ''Saint Michael triumphant over th