iff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |archivedate=5 December 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Old Water Tower Cardiff Central Station 2005.jpg|75px]]\n! Giant Daffodils\n| Mural\n| [[Water Tower, Cardiff Central Station|Cardiff Central Water Tower]]\n| 1984\n| {{sort|Bridge|Dennis Bridge {{small|(team&nbsp;leader)}}}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| Work was carried out in June 2012 to repaint the tower in beige and brown.<ref>{{cite news|last=Henry|first=Graham|title=Cardiff Central's landmark water tower renovation starts \u2013 without a daffodil in sight|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2012/06/19/cardiff-central-s-landmark-water-tower-renovation-starts-without-a-daffodil-in-sight-91466-31215727/|accessdate=26 July 2012|newspaper=Wales Online|date=19 June 2012}}</ref> \n|<ref>{{cite news|last=McWatt|first=Julia|title=Cardiff Central station water tower decoration plans slammed by painter|work=South Wales Echo|date=26 November 2011|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/2011/11/26/cardiff-central-station-water-tower-decoration-plans-slammed-by-painter-91466-29844443/|accessdate=1 April 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Grecian woman statue, Prince of Wales, St Mary St.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Grecian Woman''\n| Statue in niche\n| The [[Prince of Wales Theatre, Cardiff|Prince of Wales]] public House (formerly a theatre), [[St. Mary Street/High Street|St Mary Street]]\n| {{sort|1920|{{circa|1920}}}}\n| {{centre|{{--}}}}\n| {{centre|{{--}}}}\n| Installed when the building was a theatre<ref>{{cite web|title=Prince of Wales (Cardiff)|url=http://www.theatrestrust.org.uk/resources/theatres/show/69-prince-of-wales-cardiff|publisher=The Theatres Trust|accessdate=25 May 2014}}</ref>\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/pmsa-database/11661/|title=Statue of Grecian female|work=National Recording Project|publisher=Public Monument and Sculpture Association|accessdate=4 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105034112/http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/pmsa-database/11661/|archive-date=5 January 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:John Batchelor statue, The Hayes, Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! {{sort|Batchelor|[[John Batchelor (politician)|John Batchelor]]}}\n| Statue\n| [[The Hayes]]\n| {{sort|1884|1883\u20136}}\n| {{sort|Griffith|[[James Milo Griffith]]}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| The statue of this [[Liberal Party (UK)|Liberal]] politician roused opposition from his opponents when it was first erected. The [[Cardiff Council|council]] was presented with a petition for its removal and, in 1887, the statue was daubed with coal tar and paint.\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/pmsa-database/11719/ |title=Statue of John Batchelor |publisher=Public Monument and Sculpture Association |accessdate=7 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304084440/http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/pmsa-database/11719/ |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Statue of John, Marquis of Bute, Knight of the Thistle, in Callaghan Square, Cardiff.jpg|75px]]\n! {{sort|Bute|[[John Crichton-Stuart, 2nd Marquess of Bute]]}}\n| Statue\n| [[Callaghan Square]]\n| {{sort|1850|1848\u201353}}\n| [[John Evan Thomas]]\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| Originally located in front of the old Town Hall in [[St. Mary Street/High Street|St Mary Street]] and moved to Callaghan Square in 2000.<ref>{{cite news|title=100 facts you (probably) didn't know about Cardiff (No. 65) |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/expats/expats-newsletter/page.cfm?objectid=15864263&method=full&siteid=50082 |accessdate=7 April 2013 |newspaper=Walesonline (Expats Newsletter) |date=17 June 2002 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101222084657/http://www.walesonline.co.uk/expats/expats-newsletter/page.cfm?objectid=15864263&method=full&siteid=50082 |archivedate=22 December 2010 }}</ref> \n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pmsa.org.uk/pmsa-database/11646/|archi