fton}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|\n|<ref name=\"CPAR 22\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |title=Cardiff Public Art Register |publisher=Cardiff Council |year=2011 |page=22 |accessdate=25 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205093528/https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |archivedate=5 December 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Landsea Square fountain.JPG|75px]]\n! Landsea Square Water Feature\n| Sculpture\n| Landsea Square\n| 2000\n| \n|align=\"center\"| Jo Johnson Landscape Architects \n|\n|<ref name=\"CPAR 27\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |title=Cardiff Public Art Register |publisher=Cardiff Council |year=2011 |page=27 |accessdate=25 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205093528/https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |archivedate=5 December 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[File:Lighthouse - geograph-1866036-by-John-Lord.jpg|75px]] \n! Lighthouse<br/>(''Blue Beacon'')\n| Sculpture\n| [[Cardiff Bay Police Station]]\n| 2009\n| {{sort|Renn|Mark Renn}}\n| {{centre|{{--}}}}\n| 60 feet tall steel sculpture of a lighthouse (with blue flashing light) commissioned by [[South Wales Police]] at a cost of \u00a375,000. \n|<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/police-criticised-buying-75000-lighthouse-6293943|title=Police criticised for buying \u00a375,000 lighthouse sculpture |work=Wales Online|date=11 November 2013 |accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://rennassociates.co.uk/landmarks/ |title=Landmarks: Blue Beacon, Cardiff |publisher=Mark Renn & Associates |accessdate=3 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[File:Looking Both Ways - David Kemp geograph-5253073-by-