iff]]\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Clapperton|Thomas John Clapperton}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\">{{Harvnb|Newman|1995|loc=228}}</ref><ref name=\"British Association\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Prehistoric Period by Gilbert Bayes, National Museum Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Prehistoric Period''\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Bayes|[[Gilbert Bayes]]}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Classic Period by Gilbert Bayes, National Museum Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Classic Period''\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Bayes|[[Gilbert Bayes]]}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Medieval Period by R. L. Garbe, National Museum Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Medieval Period''\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Garbe|Richard Louis Garbe}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Modern Period by R. L. Garbe, National Museum Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Modern Period''\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Garbe|Richard Louis Garbe}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Learning by T. J. Clapperton, National Museum Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Learning''\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Clapperton|Thomas John Clapperton}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\">{{Harvnb|Newman|1995|loc=228}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Art by Bertram Pegram, National Museum Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Art''\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Pegram|Bertram Pegram}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\">{{Harvnb|Newman|1995|loc=228}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Music by David Evans, National Museum Cardiff.JPG|75px]]\n! ''Music''\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Evans|David Evans}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\">{{Harvnb|Newman|1995|loc=228}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:National Museum of Wales Cardiff.jpg|75px]]\n! Dragons and Lions\n| Architectural sculpture\n| National Museum Cardiff\n| {{sort|1914|1914\u201315}}\n| {{sort|Pegram|Bertram Pegram}}\n| Smith and Brewer\n|<ref name=\"Newman 228\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Statue Lord Ninian1.jpg|75px]]\n! {{sort|Crichton-Stuart|[[Lord Ninian Crichton-Stuart]]}}\n| Statue\n| Gorsedd Gardens\n| {{sort|1917|1915\u20139}}\n| {{sort|John|Sir [[William Goscombe John]]}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/AH/CARDIFF017.htm |title=Statue of Lord Ninian Crichton Stuart |publisher=Public Monument and Sculpture Association |accessdate=11 March 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101208144728/http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/AH/CARDIFF017.htm |archive-date=8 December 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Welsh National War Memorial, Cathays Park.jpg|75px]]\n! [[Welsh National War Memorial]]\n| Memorial\n| Alexandra Gardens\n| {{sort|1926|1924\u20138}}\n| {{sort|Pegram|Bertram Pegram}}\n| {{sort|Comper|Sir [[Ninian Comper]]}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/AH/CARDIFF129.htm |title=Welsh National War Memorial |publisher=Public Monument and Sculpture Association |accessdate=11 March 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100918072714/http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/AH/CARDIFF129.htm |archive-date=18 September 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Statue of Third Marquess of Bute, Cardiff.jpg|75px]]\n! {{sort|Bute|[[John Crichton-Stuart, 3rd Marquess of Bute]]}}\n| Statue\n| Friary Gardens\n| 1930\n| {{sort|MacGillivray|[[James Pittendrigh Macgillivray]]}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/AH/CARDIFF019.htm |title=Statue of Third Marquess of Bute |publisher=Public Monument and Sculpture Association |