41616/http://pmsa.cch.kcl.ac.uk/pmsa-database/11800/ |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:The clock, St Mary St, Cardiff.jpg|75px]]\n! Pierhead Clock\n| Clock\n| St Mary Street\n| 2011\n| {{sort|Forrest|Marianne Forrest}}\n| {{centre|{{--}}}}\n| The clock mechanism, dating to 1897, was formerly used by the clock of the [[Pierhead Building]]. It was replaced in 1973 and sold to an American collector, who decided to return it to Cardiff in 2005. The monkeys on swinging on the pendulums are a reference to the 3rd Marquess of Bute's opposition to Darwin's theory of evolution.\n|<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/cardiffonline/cardiff-news/2011/11/09/historic-pierhead-clock-makes-timely-return-to-cardiff-91466-29743876/ |title=Historic Pierhead Clock makes timely return to Cardiff |first=Wayne |last=Nowaczyk |work=South Wales Echo |date=9 November 2011 |accessdate=31 March 2013}}</ref>\n|- \n| [[File:Sir Tasker Watkins VC.jpg|75px]]\n! {{sort|Watkins|Sir [[Tasker Watkins]]}}\n| Statue\n| Outside the [[Millennium Stadium]]\n| 2009\n| {{sort|Andrews|Roger Andrews}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|\n|<ref name=\"CPAR 44\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |title=Cardiff Public Art Register |publisher=Cardiff Council |year=2011 |page=44 |accessdate=25 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205093528/https://www.cardiff.gov.uk/ENG/resident/Planning/Documents/The%20Cardiff%20Public%20Art%20Register.pdf |archivedate=5 December 2014 }}</ref>\n|- \n| \n! ''Untitled''\n| Sculpture\n| The Hayes (south)\n| 1972&nbsp;/<br/>2019-20\n| {{sort|Evans Garth|[[Garth Evans]]}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|40-metre long black steel sculpture commissioned by the [[Peter Stuyvesant (cigarette)|Peter Stuyvesant]] Foundation in 1972 and exhibited for 6 months. Returned to The Hayes in September 2019 for another 6 months.\n|<ref>{{c