r\"/><ref name=SFFUkW/><ref name=\"ideologicalsplits\"/><br>[[Euroscepticism]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Arsenyi Svynarenko|url=http://www.politiikasta.fi/kolumni/ukraine%E2%80%99s-political-landscape-shifting|title=Ukraine's political landscape is shifting|work=Politiikasta.fi|date=29 August 2014|accessdate=28 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924075340/http://www.politiikasta.fi/kolumni/ukraine%E2%80%99s-political-landscape-shifting|archivedate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=PAE/><br>[[Centrism]]<ref name=PAE>{{cite web|url=http://www.parties-and-elections.eu/ukraine.html|title=Ukraine|date=2014|work=Parties and Elections in Europe|first=Wolfram|last=Nordsieck|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612211142/http://parties-and-elections.eu/ukraine.html|archivedate=12 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref><br>[[Regionalism (politics)|Regionalism]]<ref name=PAE/><ref>{{Citation |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pyWpKKlukLcC&pg=PA205&dq=#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=After Independence:Making and Protecting the Nation in Postcolonial and Postcommunist States |first=Lowell |last=Barrington |publisher=University of Michigan Press |year=2006 |isbn=978-0472068982 |page=205}}</ref><br>[[Russophilia]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/easternapproaches/2012/10/ukrainian-politics-1|title=Viktor Yanukovych's party claims victory|publisher=The Economist|date=29 October 2012|accessdate=7 October 2015}}</ref>\n| international = \n| regional = [[United Russia]] (2005\u20132014)<ref>[https://www.rbc.ru/politics/03/07/2005/5703bafc9a7947afa08c832d Party of Regions of Ukraine and \"United Russia\" will cooperate (\u041f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u044f \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0438 \"\u0415\u0434\u0438\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\" \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0443\u0442 \u0441\u043e\u0442\u0440\u0443\u0434\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0430\u0442\u044c)]